casebody.data:
Michael MCKINZY, Appellant,
v.
Carletha GASTON (McKinzy), Respondent. WD 81013 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. Filed: June 26, 2018
Motion for Rehearing and/or Transfer to Supreme Court Denied July 31, 2018
Application for Transfer Denied September 25, 2018 Michael E. McKinzy, Sr., Overland Park, Appellant Pro Se. Carletha Gaston, Kansas City, respondent pro se. Before Division One: Lisa White Hardwick, Presiding Judge, Thomas H. Newton and Edward R. Ardini, Jr., Judges

ORDER

Per Curiam Michael McKinzy ("Father") appeals from the circuit court's judgment ordering him to pay a combined arrearage of child support and maintenance to his former wife, Carletha McKinzy ("Mother"). Father contends the court erred in denying his request to set aside the original administrative order for his child support obligation as void due to lack of proper service of process in the administrative proceeding. For reasons explained herein, we affirm.

AFFIRMED. Rule 84.16(b)
